Georgia; Declaration of Disaster Loan Area


The above-numbered Declaration is hereby amended, in accordance with notices from the Federal Emergency Management
Agency dated August 16 and August 23, 1994, to include Oglethorpe County in the State of Georgia as a disaster area as
a result of damages caused by severe storms and flooding resulting from Tropical Storm Alberto beginning on July 3,
1994 and continuing through July 25, 1994, and to extend the deadline for filing applications for physical damages.
The deadline is hereby extended thirty days to October 4, 1994.
In addition, application for economic injury loans from small businesses located in the contiguous counties of Clarke,
Elbert, Greene, Madison, Oconee, Taliaferro, and Wikes in the State of Georgia may be filed until the specified date
at the previously designated location.
All other information remains the same, i.e., the termination date for filing applications for economic injury is
April 7, 1995.
The economic injury number for Georgia is 829300.



(Catalog of Federal Domestic Assistance Program Nos. 59002 and 59008)



Dated: August 30, 1994.


<SIGNER>
Bernard Kulik,

